</style>
<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know Brookfield and the western acreage corridor well. Selling here is a different discipline to selling suburban property. Buyers are typically choosing a lifestyle as much as a house, so the campaign needs to convey what living on the property actually feels like: the morning light through the gum trees, the walk to the showgrounds for the markets, the practical fact that you can drive to the CBD in less than half an hour. Photography, video and the way I introduce buyers to the suburb all matter here.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Brookfield's housing stock is varied, from established homesteads on flat one-acre blocks close to the village, through to architecturally designed contemporary homes in the Upper Brookfield pockets with significant outlook and privacy. The Brookfield State School catchment, properties within easy reach of the showgrounds, and homes with usable level land for pool, garden or equestrian use consistently sit at the upper end of suburb values.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
